Name: Corona Extra 12pk
Description: With a refreshing, smooth taste balanced between heavier European imports and lighter domestic beer, Corona is an even-keeled cerveza with fruity-honey aromas and a touch of malt. The flavor is crisp, clean and well balanced between hops and malt, a superior taste profile from superior ingredients—the finest-quality blend of filtered water, malted barley, hops, corn and yeast.

Name: Corona Extra 18pk
Short description:
18 x 355ml Bottles
Brewed and bottled in Mexico by Grupo Modelo, Corona is the world's number 1 Mexican beer - a refreshing blend of the finest quality blend of barley, yeast, imported hops and water. Corona has a smooth, refreshing taste and well-rounded character with a pleasant malt and hop aroma. Corona is perfectly complemented when served with a wedge of lime.

Name: Heineken 15x330ml
Short description: Heineken is the world's number one premium and most global beer brand.

Name: Asahi 12x330ml
Short description: With its refreshing barley flavour and crisp aftertaste, Asahi Super Dry is by far the most popular high-quality beer in Japan. Since its debut in 1987 as Japan's first dry beer, it has continued to improve the taste and excitement of beer. Its taste has set a new standard that is acknowledged around the world today.

Name: Becks 12x330ml
Short description: Sold in over 120 countries world-wide, Beck’s is to this day brewed according to Reinheitsgebot – the German Purity Law - and states that only 4 natural ingredients can be used in its brewing; barley, hops, yeast and water. Best served extremely cold, Beck’s is full of character and instantly recognisable by its pure, crisp and fresh taste, with a slightly bitter aroma.

Name: Peroni 12x330ml
Short description: Peroni Nastro Assuro is Italy's number one premium beer. It is brewed using the finest hops, two row spring planted barley and contains 25% Italian maize, including the proprietary variety Nostrano Dell'Isola. Effortlessly stylish this Mediterranean style lager delivers an unmistakable crisp, refreshing taste and a fine subtle aroma.

Name: Ice Lager 15x330ml
Short description: A clean, fresh and distinctive ice beer, Lion Ice is ice-brewed, a centuries-old German brewing method known as ‘Eisbock’. This special brewing process involves chilling the beer in ice chambers, causing crystals to form.

Name: Export Gold 15x330ml
Short description: A golden lager characterised by a pleasant, slightly fruity flavour with a clean, crisp finish. Made using only the finest New Zealand hops, barley and pure spring water, it is perhaps New Zealand’s freshest and most refreshing beer. Export gold is best served ice cold to enhance its drinkability and refreshing flavours.

Name: Lion Red 24x330ml
Short description: Lion Red is one New Zealand's oldest beers and is full bodied, malt flavoured beer that is balanced with a pleasant hop bitterness that appeals to all beer drinkers.

Name: Speight's 24x330ml
Short description: Speight’s is the beer of choice after a hard day’s work. Probably the least sweet of all New Zealand beers, this characteristic allows the full flavour of the malt and hops to shine through. Speight’s Gold Medal Ale is a great accompaniment to any meat dish and is superb with Southern game dishes such as venison, duck and rabbit.

Name: Steinlager 24x330ml
Short description: Steinlager Classic’s international award-winning taste is envied by brewers the world over. Steinlager Classic has a robust hop nose of fresh-cut green grass and a full flavour delivered by the green bullet hop, grown in Nelson at 41 degrees latitude, the perfect hop-growing location. The body of Steinlager Classic delivers a full flavour that is perfectly balanced with a dry, tangy finish and crisp clean bitterness.

Name: Tui 15x330ml
Short description: Tui East India Pale Ale is a light, crisp, and delicately malted beer. After opening the screw cap and nursing your torn finger you should notice a distinct aroma of the Mangatainoka River. No? Rest the bottle neck gently under your nostril and give it another sniff, you’ll get it.

Short description:

Name: Teacher 1 litre
Short description: It is said that William Teacher would not give his name to his blend until he had found perfection. Highland Cream is that whisky. It uses fully smoked peat single malt whisky from The Ardmore distillery as its fingerprint whisky. This gives it incredible depth and smoothness combined with a rich smokey undertone.

Name: Dewar's 1 litre
Short description: A hugely popular entry level whisky first created over a century ago. It contains around 40 different whiskies in the blend, with Aberfeldy at its heart.

Name: Kingfisher 12x330ml
Short description: Kingfisher Beer Premium Lager Beer 12pk

Name: Ranfurly 18x440ml Cans
Short description: A traditional draught beer, Ranfurly Draught has developed a strong relationship with ‘The Ranfurly Man’ over the years. A real character, drawn from the heartland, ‘The Ranfurly Man’ brings out the tough in all of us.

Name: Lion Brown 18x330ml Cans
Short description: Lion Brown was first known as Imperial Draught Ale, before being nick named ‘The Brown Bomber’ by servicemen in the forties and later taking on that name in 1950. Established as Lion Brown from 1953, it was originally served only from the tap- a unique barrel shaped stand that became an icon in pubs around the country. Lion Brown is a deep amber beer with a nutty, biscuity note. Its hoppy nose is balanced with a hint of sweetness which refreshes the palate.

Name: Flame 15x330ml
Short description: Extreme measures go into making this popular beer. In fact the process used to make Flame is called ‘extreme brewing’. Malt and hops are first subjected to extreme heat and then concentrated to retain the flavour. The process ends with the beer being ‘crash cooled’ to sub-zero temperatures resulting in a smoother, easy drinking, full strength beer. Flame is a moderately bittered, full-bodied lager style beer. The beer is nicely balanced and has light refreshing fruity notes in the flavour and aftertaste. Whether it’s hot or cold outside, Flame is a favourite of those who appreciate a well-crafted unique beer.

Name: Haagen Lager 15x330ml
Short description: Haagen is an award-winning German-styled award premium lager made with natural New Zealand ingredients to create a crisp and refreshing beer for all occasions.

Name: NZ Pure 12x330ml
Short description: NZ PURE is a premium, naturally brewed 5% lager that contains no additives or preservatives. NZ PURE – Purify your world.

Short description: At the heart of Steinlager Classic is the idea of challenge. Steinlager Classic’s international award-winning taste is envied by brewers the world over.

Name: St Remy 1 litre
Short description: Amber colour with golden highlights. The blend of the fruitiness and the “acid drop” of the eau-de-vie reveal notes of cherries and raspberries with touches of vanilla and oak. A very complex brandy thanks to richness of the distillates from the French vineyards. First strong and dry, then rounded with a fine complexity. Red fruits aromas, vanilla and woody notes. Suave and well balanced.

Name: woodstock 18x330ml 5%
Short description: The iconic Woodstock Brand offers New Zealand’s leading range of Bourbon products including the countries largest selling RTD brand. It is distilled, blended and aged at one of Kentucky’s oldest registered distilleries deep in the heart of bourbon country. The raw whiskey is aged in new American white oak barrels until it has developed the smoothness and complexity of flavours needed to proudly bear the Woodstock name.

Name: Effen Raspberry 10pk Bottles 330ml
Short description: EFFEN is Dutch for “smooth, even, and balanced,” and was created for those who are deliberate about every detail they choose. From their clothes and clubs, to their cocktails and company they keep. EFFEN Vodka wasn’t just distilled for them—it was designed for them. This divine premix is a blend of EFFEN vodka, sparkling water and a hint of raspberry. ABV: 4.8%\n

Utilising temperature-sensitive ink technology, fans will be reminded that “Winter is Here” from an unexpected graphic icy reveal on the bottle when frozen. \n \n

Name: KAHLUA SALTED CARAMEL 1 LTR
Short description: Kahlua Salted Caramel Liqueur 1ltr. Blends the tasty combination of salty and sweet. The decadent and smooth notes of salted caramel balance perfectly with the taste of Kahlua, allowing for a sweet indulgence that is reminiscent of simple pleasures and good times.
